  <headingLevel value="subheadinga"/>
  <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color:#007FAD;"&gt;LOCATION AND STRUCTURE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</text>
</STATIC_heading>
  </block>
  <block refid="991f3364-8554-4a95-9ef8-8ec02d5b1555">
    <STATIC_text>
  <text>&lt;p&gt;Label Figure 18-6.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;adrenal glands&lt;/strong&gt; are two small glands, one on top of each &lt;strong&gt;kidney &lt;/strong&gt;[1]. Each gland consists of two parts: an outer portion, the &lt;strong&gt;adrenal cortex&lt;/strong&gt; [2], and an inner portion, the&lt;strong&gt; adrenal medulla&lt;/strong&gt; [3]. The adrenal cortex and the adrenal medulla are two glands in one, secreting different hormones. The adrenal cortex secretes &lt;strong&gt;steroids &lt;/strong&gt;or &lt;strong&gt;corticosteroids &lt;/strong&gt;(complex chemicals derived from cholesterol); the adrenal medulla secretes &lt;strong&gt;catecholamines &lt;/strong&gt;(chemicals derived from amino acids).&lt;/p&gt;</text>
</STATIC_text>
  </block>
